Inline features

You can declare HTML entities by name (ex: €), by decimal code point (ex: €), or by hexadecimal code point (ex: €). Here we have examples of text in bold and emphasised and monospaced and in small-caps and with superscripts and subscripts. You may also correct perfectbroken text. Also, all of this emphasised text should appear on the same line.

Here is a link to section number 1 or smartly, Section 1. And here is a link to that same section. You can also link to Tip #1, or smarly Tip  #1, or a link to that same tip. The bibliography is at the end[1][2][3]. You can also place multiple citations in the same square brackets[1,2,3]. There is also(1) a list(2) of notes(3), which if you prefer you can reference them with a single command(1,2,3).
